cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with improving the interpretability of features learned by neural network classifiers in medical applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of adversarial robustness in the training process also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of feature interpretability using class activation maps and saliency maps suggests that the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
